    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-10-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="155"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2072.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-10-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 8, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch of the 23d ultimo,
                    No. 1457, informing me of the transfer of Colonels Nagle and Warren from
                    Kilmainham jail to Mountjoy prison.</p>
                <p>Thanking you for your attention in keeping me informed upon the subject, I trust
                    that you will follow these cases up with renewed urgency.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM IL SEWARD</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
